cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use FusionBench, please cite it."
title: "FusionBench: when is multi-model fusion worth it?"
abstract: >-
  A cost-aware harness and public catalog that measures, per task type and at
  matched compute, which multi-model fusion recipe (panel + judge + synthesizer)
  is worth its cost over a single model or self-MoA, using a complementarity
  prefilter to keep the search cheap.
authors:
  - name: "Ion"
version: 0.0.1
date-released: 2026-06-14
license: MIT
url: "https://github.com/yourname/fusionbench"
keywords:
  - llm
  - model-fusion
  - mixture-of-agents
  - evaluation
  - benchmark
